BFN 

  [Text] Moscow June 24 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin met President of the Commission of the European Union 
Jacques Delors and German Chancellor Helmut Kohl at the Kerkira 
mayor's office today to discuss the implementation of the 
Russian-European agreement, major projects of economic 
cooperation and prospects for the Russian joining of the G7 
activities, the press service of the Russian state head reports. 
  The meeting with Helmut Kohl also discussed aspects of 
Russian- German relations, says the press service. "The sides 
coordinated the program of joint participation in the seeing-off 
ceremony for Russian troops withdrawn from Germany to be held on 
August 31," reports the press service. 

